  "prompt": "Whom was Muhammad worshipping before getting revelations?",
  "response": "Before receiving revelations from Allah, Muhammad was part of the polytheistic society of Mecca, where the predominant religion involved the worship of multiple deities and idols. The Kaaba, a central shrine in Mecca, housed various idols that represented different gods worshipped by the tribes of Arabia. While Muhammad was exposed to this polytheistic environment, he was known to have a monotheistic inclination and often reflected on the nature of God. Historical accounts suggest that he rejected the idolatry practiced by his society and sought a deeper spiritual understanding long before receiving his first revelation from the angel Gabriel at the age of 40.",
